parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to seize or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel seizes or freezes
the power steering pump fails
the rack and pinion unit fails
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
especially at low speeds.

the steering wheel seizes or freezes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of control, especially when driving on inclines or at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle rolls backward on inclines
the transmission fails to downshift
the vehicle's speed decreases despite throttle input
and the vehicle experiences sudden and violent shuddering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure to engage properly can cause the vehicle to roll backward on inclines, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of control, especially when driving on inclines or at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backward on inclines
the transmission fails to engage
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
and the vehicle experiences sudden and violent shuddering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission intermittent failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of control, especially when driving on inclines or at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the vehicle experiences sudden and violent shuddering
and the transmission fails to downshift.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward at a high rate of speed
often when braking or accelerating from a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty heated seat can be a fire hazard and cause discomfort to the driver.
symptoms: The heated seat stops working or fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of important vehicle information, leading to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The instrument cluster fails to display information
or the display is washed out in sunlight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system failure can cause a fire, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often in the trunk or electrical wiring system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A strong, unexplained odor can be a sign of a larger problem and may cause discomfort or distraction to the driver.
symptoms: A strong
unexplained odor is present inside the vehicle
often coming from the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty main electrical harness can cause a range of problems, including electrical system failures and fires.
symptoms: The main electrical harness fails
requiring replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
the brake pedal does not disengage cruise control
the vehicle surges forward
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the engine races even when pressure is removed from the accelerator pedal.
